title: Pride and Prejudice
author: Jane Austen
description: A sharp-witted exploration of manners, marriage and morality in early 19th-century England.

author: George Orwell
description: A chilling depiction of totalitarian surveillance and state control.

title: The Great Gatsby
author: F. Scott Fitzgerald
description: An examination of the American Dream through wealth, love, and illusion.

title: To Kill a Mockingbird
author: Harper Lee
description: A young girl's view of racial injustice and moral growth in the American South.

title: The Hobbit
author: J.R.R. Tolkien
description: Bilbo Baggins' unexpected journey that sets the stage for epic tales to follow.

title: The Name of the Wind
author: Patrick Rothfuss
description: An adventurer and musician recounts his life, magic and tragedies.

title: Beloved
author: Toni Morrison
description: A former slave confronts haunting memories and a past that refuses to die.

title: Invisible Cities
author: Italo Calvino
description: A poetic meditation composed of imagined cities described to a famous explorer.

title: The Catcher in the Rye
author: J.D. Salinger
description: A teenager's candid account of alienation and identity in postwar America.

title: Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind
author: Yuval Noah Harari
description: A sweeping narrative of human evolution, culture, and impact.

title: The Silent Garden
author: Maya Hart
description: A detective returns to her hometown to investigate a string of disappearances tied to a neglected estate.

title: The Glass Ocean
author: Liam O'Reilly
description: Interwoven lives aboard ships crossing the Atlantic during turbulent times.

title: Moonlit Orchard
author: Aisha Rahman
description: Generational tensions and secrets unfold on a rural orchard in South Asia.

title: Quantum Hearts
author: Ethan Cole
description: A scientist and an AI navigate love and ethical dilemmas in a near-future lab.

title: The Last Orchard
author: Sven Larsson
description: A dying ecosystem forces a community to confront past choices and rebuild.

title: Crimson Streets
author: Nora Kline
description: A gritty detective unravels corruption across a metropolis where nothing is what it seems.

title: House of Paper
author: Isabella Moretti
description: A family home literally keeps the memories of its occupants bound in paper books.

title: Children of Dust
author: R. K. Singh
description: Lives shattered and remade during a tumultuous period of migration and division.

title: Echoes in Amber
author: Claire Dupont
description: A wartime love story told through letters and lost heirlooms.

title: The Algorithm's Child
author: Hiro Tanaka
description: A parent's struggle to raise a child shaped in part by algorithmic social systems.

title: The Paper Lantern
author: Mei Lin
description: A teen navigates identity and tradition during a transformative summer.

title: Shadows Over Meridian
author: Derek Hale
description: Hidden magic in modern streets leads to a war between old families.

title: The Cartographer's Daughter
author: Ana Sousa

title: Paper Tigers
author: Marcus Bell
description: Two friends confront aging, loss, and the small rebellions that keep them alive.

title: Starlight Protocol
author: Nadia Petrova
description: Interstellar politics collide with personal loyalties aboard a fleet on the edge of war.

title: The Velvet Key
author: Lena Alvarez
description: A crumbling manor, a missing heir, and secrets hidden in velvet-lined drawers.

title: Fragments of Light
author: Oluwaseun Adeyemi
description: A culturally rich future where technology and tradition intertwine.

title: Midnight's Orchard
author: Priya Menon
description: Two former lovers reunite at an orchard that holds shared memories and regrets.

title: Atlas of Small Wonders

description: An intimate collection of essays about overlooked places and brief encounters.

title: Broken Compass
author: Hannah Brooks
description: A journalist uncovers a conspiracy that puts her life and world view at risk.

title: River of Glass
